   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <note class="- topic/note ">This is the bottom entry procedure. See <xref href="Install_the_Parallel_Board_0H1545_in_25-50_kVA_Systems_Top_Entry_TSK_0000195495.dita"
                  format="dita"
                  scope="local"
                  type="task"
                  class="- topic/xref "/> for the top entry procedure.</note>
         <hazardstatement type="danger" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
            <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
               <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
               <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">
                  <sl class="- topic/sl ">
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Electrical equipment must be installed, operated, serviced, and
maintained only by qualified personnel.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Apply appropriate personal protective equipment (PPE) and follow
safe electrical work practices.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Disconnection devices for AC and DC must be provided by others,
be readily accessible, and the function of the disconnect device marked
for its function.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Turn off all power supplying the UPS system before working on
or inside the equipment.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">Before working on the UPS system, check for hazardous voltage
between all terminals including the protective earth.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">The UPS contains an internal energy source. Hazardous voltage
can be present even when disconnected from the mains supply. Before
installing or servicing the UPS system, ensure that the units are
OFF and that mains and batteries are disconnected. Wait five minutes
before opening the UPS to allow the capacitors to discharge.</sli>
                     <sli class="- topic/sli ">The UPS must be properly earthed/grounded and due to a high leakage
current, the earthing/grounding conductor must be connected first.</sli>
                  </sl>
               </howtoavoid>
            </messagepanel>
         </hazardstatement>
         <note class="- topic/note ">This procedure is only applicable
to 25–50 kVA systems.</note>
         <note class="- topic/note ">The procedure is the same
for UPS1 and UPS2 in the parallel system.</note>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the two indicated covers in front of and below the
breakers.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_removebreakercover__w120mm_0000195476.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Slide out the low voltage assembly far enough to disconnect
the cables.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Note the location of the cables and disconnect the cables.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_removelowvoltagepart__w120mm_0000195475.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the indicated cover.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/replace_0j-0n-0914_37kw-fanass_removecover_w120mm_0000191448.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         xml:lang="en"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the cover in front of the connection box interface.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_removecoverinfrontofparallelboardarea_w120mm_0000195474.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tilt the interface assembly outwards.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_tiltinterfaceassembleforover_w120mm_0000195473.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the indicated metal plate.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_removemetalpart_w120mm_0000195472.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Mount the 0P2558 PCB assembly to the bracket using four
M4 screws and attach four wire clips to the bracket.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_assembleboard_w120mm_0000195471.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Install the 0P2558 PCB assembly in the UPS using the M6
screw and press the assembly onto the power board flange as illustrated.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_install0p2558_pcba_board_w120mm_0000195470.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the terminators from the lowest power module and
reconnect them into the 0P2558 PCB assembly.</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Remove the green, yellow and red terminators from the
lowest power module.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Discard the red terminator and plug the green terminator
into terminal A1 (UPS1) / A2 (UPS2), and the yellow terminator into
B1 (UPS1) / B2 (UPS2).</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_ups1moveterminators_w120mm_0000195469.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect the 0W11666 cables to the original locations of
the RJ45 terminators on the power module, and route and connect the
cables to the parallel board.</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect cable P2 (red) to J2006 on the parallel board.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect cable P3 (green) to J2002 on the parallel board.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect cable P4 (yellow) to J2005 on the parallel board.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_install0w11666cable_w120mm_0000195468.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect the 0W6341 cable (7000 mm long) to the remaining
green and yellow terminals.</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect A2 (green) on UPS1 to A1 (green) on UPS2.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Connect B2 (yellow) on UPS1 to B1 (yellow) on UPS2.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_install0w63341cabletoboard_w120mm_0000195467.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Route the 0W6341 cable behind the inner side plate, out
through the grommet in the low voltage channel, and out through the
bottom conduit plate to the other UPS.</cmd>
            <stepxmp class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepxmp ">
               <fig class="- topic/fig ">
                  <image href="../Images/install_0h-1544_parallelboard-25-50kw_bottomrouteof-0w6341_w120mm_0000195486.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"
                         class="- topic/image "/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Reinstall the removed covers, cables and plates in reversed
order.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Configure the settings for parallel operation, see <xref href="Parallel_Configuration_REF_0000195493.dita"
                     format="dita"
                     scope="local"
                     type="reference"
                     class="- topic/xref "/>.</cmd>
         </step>
      </steps>
